result.execSummary:
The defendant Dustin Michael Feeney was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dustin Michael Feeney is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dustin Michael Feeney was found guilty of Battery [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Dustin Michael Feeney was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: Lundell, RPR: Val Deiss, Clerk: Webb, ADA: Kenneth N. Sortedahl   DF ATTY: Joseph R. Caton, DF:  Dustin Michael Feeney appeared.  Court called at 4:04 p.m. *COURT QUASHES COMMITMENT ORDER FOR NON-PAYMENT*   Includes case 14CM486 & 15CM51.  Set for PTC.  DE files a Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights Form with the Court.  Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea.  Court reads charge and maximum penalty.  DE pleads No Contest to Ct 1 W/O the Domestic Abuse Enhancer in 15CM51.  DE pleads No Contest to the Amended Ct. 3 Disorderly Conduct W/O the Domestic Abuse Enhancer in 15CM51.   Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE adjguilty of Ct 1 W/O the Domestic Abuse Enhancer and the Amended Ct. 3 (Disorderly Conduct) W/O the Domestic Abuse Enhancer in 15CM51. On motion of the State, Crt dismisses Ct 2 & Ct 4 in 15CM51 & 14CM486. Sentencing arguments. DE makes statement.  Crt orders:

S/W  2 years with conditions  
- Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times while this case is ongoing. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.
- It is hereby ordered, in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO ABUSIVE CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations, Pamela Gruber and Ashley Lewis.  The term "abusive contact" is hereby defined as a verbal assault or an intentional infliction of or threat to inflict physical pain, physical injury or illness, an impairment of physical condition, and /or sexual contact or sexual intercourse without consent.  
- DE ordered to take medication as prescribed by his physicians
- DE ordered to attend mental health treatment 
- DE ordered to complete all counseling
- Court orders $675 to be stricken from the committment order and two of the warrant fees waived.
- Court costs of $486.00 apply money on file
- DE to report to probation no later than 04/21/2015 by 4:00 p.m. 
- DE to meet with the payment clerk after reporting to probation on 04/21/2015.
- 20 days to appeal
Status conference on April 20, 2015 at 03:30 pm.
